Slovenia Targets 2011 Budget Deficit of 4.7% of GDP, Pahor Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-09-15T08:20:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/slovenia-targets-2011-budget-deficit-of-4-7-of-gdp-pahor-says.html
Slovenia is targeting a  budget
deficit  equaling 4.7 percent of gross domestic for this year,
Prime Minister Borut Pahor told lawmakers in  Ljubljana  today,
according to a live brodcast by TV Slovenija.  Lawmakers are set to vote on the ammended budget spending
by the minority government tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  